title: Historical Tales, Vol V: German
creator: Charles Morris
description: LibriVox recording of Historical Tales, Vol V: German, by Charles Morris. Read by Kalynda. Volume five of a series containing anecdotes and stories, some well-known, others less so, of particular countries. This fifth volume covers the history of Germany from its first contact with Rome up to the coronation of Emperor William, describing history for children and young adults in an exciting and novel manner. (Introduction by Kalynda) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B Part 1 (124MB) Download M4B Part 2 (98MB)
subject: germany; history; children; librivox; audiobook
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: For people, like me, more versed in Celtic and English folklore, this was an excellent book.
reviews.reviewtitle: I enjoyed this a great deal
